General Host Corp said it willreport a loss from continuing operations and a sharp decline innet income for the year ended January 25, 1987, due tosubstantial operating losses in its Frank's Nursery and Craftsunit. For the year ended January 25, 1986, General reported netincome of 29.7 mln dlrs.    The company said it discovered problems in its unit'scomputerized accounts payable system. It said results of itsother nursery and craft unit, Flower Time Inc, are notaffected. It said its accountants are investigating theproblem, which will delay release of its full-year results. Reuter&#3;